latestPosts.caption:
I don’t know why, but today I felt like sharing this. I often get requests to share my skincare routine, but I never really felt like opening up—mainly because the skin you see on camera today isn’t what it used to be.

From 2019 to 2022, my skin journey took such a toll on me that even thinking about it brings tears to my eyes. I still remember how I used to lock myself in, avoiding visits to friends and relatives. But I was lucky to have friends who never let me feel alone. They always made me feel comfortable, confident, and reminded me that I am beautiful in my own way.

Back then, I damaged my skin trying every trending product and DIY remedy I saw on bloggers’ videos. Nothing worked, and I would sit and cry, convinced that my skin would never heal. Seeing me struggle, my brother suggested I visit a Pediatric dermatologist—and I’m forever thankful to the Almighty and then to that doctor who helped me through my worst phase.

One thing I’ve learned is: accept yourself, love yourself—you are beautiful in your own way. And instead of spending money on random products, get a proper consultation from a good dermatologist in your city.

While my acne has healed, some marks are still left behind. But I wanted to share my story today in case it helps even one of you feel less alone. 💛

latestPosts.caption:
“Love Starts Within”

Don’t beg for love with outstretched hands,
In places where it rarely lands.
Don’t chase the warmth in fleeting eyes,
While your own fire slowly dies.

You are not hollow, not half-made,
Not something lost that must be saved.
You are the sun, the blooming seed—
The very love you think you need.

Let not their silence shape your worth,
Or hunger haunt your time on Earth.
For hearts that ache to be pursued,
Forget their own are worth it too.

So turn inward, softly, kind—
Meet the mirror, and you’ll find
A soul that’s battled, burned, and grown,
Deserving love that’s self-homegrown.

Be your comfort, be your peace,
Let the craving, let it cease.
For when you choose to love your name,
No empty love will feel the same.
- @tasmiyahsheikh ✨
